"{\"uid\": \"360info.org-imane-khelif-and-the-making-of-olympic-icons\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Under Creative Commons, you are free to: Share - copy and redistribute the Features and Articles from 360info in any medium or format; Adapt - remix, transform, and build upon these Features and Articles for any purpose, even commercially.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6, \"end\": 22, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons\", \"score\": 0.9994023882572374, \"rank\": 0.0005979690963803954, \"text\": \"Creative Commons\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You must: Attribute - Credit the author/s name, 360info, and the title of the work; Provide a link to theCC licence Attribution 4.0 International.\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Note: These links and credits are inserted into the File you download.\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 458, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indicate if you made any changes to the work.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The following boxes are optional to fill in.\", \"from\": 506, \"to\": 550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We ask that you fill them in if you can as they help us tell the Authors where their content is being published.\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u0394  The iconic images captured of female athletes during the 2024 Paris Olympics illustrate how far we have come but also how far we still have to go.\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 814, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The iconic images captured of female athletes during the 2024 Paris Olympics illustrate how far we have come but also how far we still have to go.\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Once again the Olympics has captivated much of the world withextraordinary feats of athleticism,glorious joy,heart-rending despair,absurd national pridealong with moments that transcend nationalism, anddevastating instances of vitriol.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 1201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the Paris Games recede and attention returns to the more banal, often diabolical, concerns of daily life, a wonderful array of striking images remain with which to remember the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From theextraordinary salute to gymnast Rebeca Andradeby Simone Biles and Jordan Chiles, to the meme inspiring coolness ofSouth Korean pistol shooter Kim Yeji, to the joy of dual gold medalist Jess Foxjumping into the waterto celebrate her sister Noemie's kayaking gold - women were at the centre of the glorious images created from the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1473, \"end\": 1486, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jordan Chiles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jordan_Chiles\"}, {\"begin\": 1527, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9997967729138311, \"rank\": 0.00020318160598564955, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6554055913356783e-18, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 1553, \"end\": 1557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5633119385262866e-23, \"text\": \"Yeji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"New@axiosfrom#Paris2024  How@GettyImagesbeams those incredible Olympic images around the world within secondshttps://t.co/4GWYMldtJ8  - Ina Fried (@inafried)August 8, 2024    You dropped this, Kim Yeji: \\ud83d\\udc51  \\ud83d\\udcf7: Korean Sport & Olympic Committeepic.twitter.com/eCNGrNP7os  - The Olympic Games (@Olympics)August 1, 2024    No\\u00e9mie Fox emulates sister Jess by winning Paris 2024 gold with kayak cross victoryhttps://t.co/nS500puas2  - Guardian Australia (@GuardianAus)August 5, 2024    Yet it is the attempted misuse of certain images which might create the most enduring legacy of these Games.\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 2337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1867, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"t.co\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 1886, \"end\": 1895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ina_Fried\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ina Fried\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ina_Fried\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ina_Fried\"}, {\"begin\": 1943, \"end\": 1946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6554055913356783e-18, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 1947, \"end\": 1951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5633119385262866e-23, \"text\": \"Yeji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\"}, {\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/20th_Century_Studios\", \"score\": 0.7345768489897527, \"rank\": 0.3613234439076825, \"text\": \"Fox\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/20th_Century_Studios\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/20th_Century_Studios\"}, {\"begin\": 2113, \"end\": 2123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2530029564562744e-25, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2134, \"end\": 2139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"score\": 0.9999931353312664, \"rank\": 6.864716051388758e-06, \"text\": \"kayak\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayak\"}, {\"begin\": 2161, \"end\": 2165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"t.co\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}, {\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2198, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guardian Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At issue are not only debates about gender and race, but also a clear illustration of the waythe moral panic about trans women harms other women as well.\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2456, \"end\": 2467, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.7896221521117759, \"rank\": 0.2664285029560523, \"text\": \"trans women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Visuals have long been central to the stories that the Olympics creates, and the stories that it seeks to tell.\", \"from\": 2494, \"to\": 2605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gender and race were at the forefront from the start.\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From its inception in 1896, the modern Olympics sought to create a powerful iconography of visual images to deify sport.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening and closing ceremonies highlighted the spectacle of the Games, while from 1908 until Melbourne in 1956, each summer Games washeralded by a postershowcasing the idealised and generally naked bodies of powerful white men.\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2878, \"end\": 2887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.5740171029894591e-12, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) votes to award the 1924 Summer Olympics to Paris, choosing the French capital ahead of Amsterdam, Los Angeles, Prague and Rome.pic.twitter.com/Dvt55sIGkp  - 1924 Live (@100YearsAgoLive)June 2, 2021    In 1936 the diminutive brown-haired Hitler brought television to Germany in order to broadcast his fascistic white supremacist vision of dominant tall blond blue-eyed men to the world - only for theAfrican American athlete Jesse Owensto famously disrupt those visions with his four gold medals as the crowd in Berlin chanted his name.\", \"from\": 3012, \"to\": 3589, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3018, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3018, \"end\": 3055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3099, \"end\": 3104, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2599229829091537e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3119, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999420431019664, \"rank\": 5.6316155209083325e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3143, \"end\": 3152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.446396754570866e-18, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}, {\"begin\": 3154, \"end\": 3165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1848770804368318e-21, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3167, \"end\": 3173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3789322591147796e-13, \"text\": \"Prague\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prague\"}, {\"begin\": 3293, \"end\": 3299, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7695734439462369e-25, \"text\": \"Hitler\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adolf_Hitler\"}, {\"begin\": 3322, \"end\": 3329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weimar_Republic\", \"score\": 0.9996150835278137, \"rank\": 0.00036007983467293154, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weimar_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Weimar_Republic\"}, {\"begin\": 3463, \"end\": 3471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999914734872, \"rank\": 8.449295803240699e-09, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3472, \"end\": 3479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athlete\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3491126047341537e-15, \"text\": \"athlete\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athlete\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athlete\"}, {\"begin\": 3567, \"end\": 3573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9999995711997154, \"rank\": 4.287829840442017e-07, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then in 1968 the iconography of the Olympics was forever altered bytwo black men - Americans John Carlos and Tommie Smith - raising their fists with pride and a call for justicein what came to be known as the Black Power salute, while a white man - Australian Peter Norman - stood alongside them in solidarity wearing the same protest badge.\", \"from\": 3591, \"to\": 3932, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3686, \"end\": 3697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Carlos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Carlos\"}, {\"begin\": 3702, \"end\": 3714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommie Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommie_Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 3802, \"end\": 3820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Olympics_Black_Power_salute\", \"score\": 0.999554387794509, \"rank\": 0.00044581086447222865, \"text\": \"Black Power salute\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Olympics_Black_Power_salute\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1968_Olympics_Black_Power_salute\"}, {\"begin\": 3842, \"end\": 3852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9942685997362034, \"rank\": 0.005613835740899777, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Powerful women, however, were conspicuous in their absence from the official images used to promote the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3934, \"to\": 4047, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, the bodies of strong athletic women have beenmore likely to attract suspicion and censure, than celebration, as the advent of 'sex testing' shows.\", \"from\": 4049, \"to\": 4203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ancient Olympics had excluded women, and the founder of the modern Olympics, Pierre de Coubertin, sought to do the same.\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4288, \"end\": 4307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pierre de Coubertin\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pierre_de_Coubertin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"De Coubertin was inspired by the British notion that sports could turn boys into good strong men.\", \"from\": 4330, \"to\": 4427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4365, \"end\": 4372, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999946060315734, \"rank\": 3.306385445067254e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Games,\\\" he proclaimed, \\\"are the solemn and periodic exaltation of male sport - with the applause of women as a reward.\", \"from\": 4429, \"to\": 4552, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"An Olympiad with females would be impractical, uninteresting, unaesthetic and improper.\\\"\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) hasrecently sought to defend de Coubertin, arguing that he was just trying to protect women from prurient spectators.\", \"from\": 4645, \"to\": 4804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4651, \"end\": 4688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4651, \"end\": 4688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, protecting women from themselves wasone of the main rationales used to exclude them from sport.\", \"from\": 4806, \"to\": 4910, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Women's bodies were too weak, too frail.\", \"from\": 4911, \"to\": 4951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletics was too dangerous, especially when it came to contact sports.\", \"from\": 4952, \"to\": 5023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Inclusion had to be fought for at every turn, despite countless Olympics revealing that the belief that there is no mass audience for women's sport is, in fact, nonsense.\", \"from\": 5025, \"to\": 5195, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A rival Olympiad for women in the 1920s spurred the IOC to reluctant concessions around athletics, but from 1928 to 1960 the percentage of female competitors only increased from 10 percent to 11 percent.\", \"from\": 5197, \"to\": 5400, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5251, \"end\": 5254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1601572605634516e-48, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite a woman running the original modern Olympics marathon course in 1896, it took until 1984 for women to be 'allowed' to compete in this event at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 5402, \"to\": 5566, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And even in 2024, when women make up half of the athletes at the Games, the length of the cycling road race for women (157.6km) was more than 100km shorter than for the men (272km).\", \"from\": 5568, \"to\": 5749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevertheless, women were at the centre of the glorious photographs created from the 2024 Olympics.\", \"from\": 5751, \"to\": 5849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was the images of one female athlete that gained the most attention: Algerian gold medal boxer Imane Khelif.\", \"from\": 5851, \"to\": 5966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the guise of protecting women, Khelif waswilfully misgendered as a manwho threatened the safety of the women she was fighting.\", \"from\": 5968, \"to\": 6097, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is no accident that the celebrities leading these disingenuous charges turned to visual images as if they provided proof of their claims.\", \"from\": 6099, \"to\": 6239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not only are pictures supposed to tell a thousand words, they arealso supposed to convey the truth.\", \"from\": 6241, \"to\": 6340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Especially when it comes to notoriously slippery notions of gender, sex, and race.\", \"from\": 6341, \"to\": 6423, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, over the last few years,pictures of athletes like Hannah Mouncey and Lia Thomashave been used by anti-trans activists to represent trans women as monstrous threats to cis women.\", \"from\": 6425, \"to\": 6607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6482, \"end\": 6496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mouncey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hannah Mouncey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13365117\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mouncey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hannah_Mouncey\"}, {\"begin\": 6563, \"end\": 6574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"score\": 0.7896221521117759, \"rank\": 0.2664285029560523, \"text\": \"trans women\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Transgender\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yet these images draw on longstanding fears of powerful women that have been used to limit the participation of many cis girls and women in sports.\", \"from\": 6609, \"to\": 6756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Martina Navratilova and Serena Williams, for example,were regularly vilified as monstrous through the use of pictures and cartoons, as if their dominant strength was unnatural and a threat to the safety of other women.\", \"from\": 6758, \"to\": 6976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6760, \"end\": 6779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martina_Navratilova\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Martina Navratilova\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martina_Navratilova\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martina_Navratilova\"}, {\"begin\": 6784, \"end\": 6799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Serena Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serena_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Underlying the misuse of such images remains idealised notions of women as weakly feminine, in need of constant protection.\", \"from\": 6978, \"to\": 7101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The broad harm of such notions of \\\"true\\\" femininity were apparentin the tears of US rugby player Ilona Maherwhose superb play was questioned, rather than celebrated, by some people due to her physical prowess.\", \"from\": 7103, \"to\": 7312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7202, \"end\": 7207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\", \"score\": 0.9999902515330588, \"rank\": 9.748561172052383e-06, \"text\": \"Ilona\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, a pair of photos of Khelif provided the most compelling iconography of the 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 7314, \"to\": 7412, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In one, we see the grace of her, and her final opponent, Yang Liu, smiling as they embrace after their gold medal bout.\", \"from\": 7414, \"to\": 7533, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7473, \"end\": 7481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"score\": 0.9999966834675861, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After all the transphobia, witch-hunting, and the despicable and unsportsmanlike disrespect shown by a handful of athletes - let THIS image be the one that stays with you:  After Imane Khelif won her gold medal bout her opponent, Yang Liu of China, embraced her with a smile.pic.twitter.com/vYjkQaailZ  - Scot \\ud83c\\uddf5\\ud83c\\uddf8 (@scotwithat)August 9, 2024    And in the other, we see Khelif saluting in glorious pride as a sovereign woman who has just won a gold medal.\", \"from\": 7535, \"to\": 7989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7716, \"end\": 7728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 7767, \"end\": 7775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"score\": 0.9999966834675861, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yang Liu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liu_Yang_(violinist)\"}, {\"begin\": 7779, \"end\": 7784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999999996052793, \"rank\": 2.225066956910153e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Imane Khelif sold scrap metal to pay for her boxing training, is a UNICEF ambassador, stood up against horrific bullying, and is now an Olympic champion.pic.twitter.com/BkvP9VEVul  - Dr. Lucky Tran (@luckytran)August 9, 2024    Iconic images of athleticism and joy indeed.\", \"from\": 7991, \"to\": 8263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7995, \"end\": 8007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 8062, \"end\": 8068, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.967910260187415e-33, \"text\": \"UNICEF\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UNICEF\"}, {\"begin\": 8182, \"end\": 8187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucky_Spencer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.158793821641908e-17, \"text\": \"Lucky\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucky_Spencer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucky_Spencer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Associate Professor Matthew Klugmanis an Australian Research Council Future Fellow at Victoria University's Institute for Health & Sport with the Community Identity and Displacement Research Network (CIDRN) and a Research Fellow in the Chief Albert Luthuli Research Program, University of South Africa.\", \"from\": 8265, \"to\": 8567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8310, \"end\": 8337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Research_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Research Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Research_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Research_Council\"}, {\"begin\": 8345, \"end\": 8351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\", \"score\": 0.5222057439434804, \"rank\": 0.7393570666891808, \"text\": \"Fellow\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Institute_of_Electrical_and_Electronics_Engineers\"}, {\"begin\": 8511, \"end\": 8517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uncle_Albert\", \"score\": 0.9999999150986731, \"rank\": 8.47735580976256e-08, \"text\": \"Albert\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uncle_Albert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uncle_Albert\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their research examines the intersecting histories of sports, emotions, race, gender, sexuality, medicine, science, migration, the visual, and bodies.\", \"from\": 8568, \"to\": 8718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Associate Professor Klugman's research has been funded by the Australian Research Council FT230100681.\", \"from\": 8720, \"to\": 8822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8786, \"end\": 8813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Research_Council\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian Research Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Research_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Research_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Originally published underCreative Commonsby360info\\u2122.\", \"from\": 8824, \"to\": 8877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With tensions between Tokyo and Beijing rising, ASEAN and Taiwan must balance economic integration with the political realities imposed by China's growing assertiveness.\", \"from\": 8879, \"to\": 9048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8905, \"end\": 8910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7209804040648814, \"rank\": 0.38700024905227937, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 8915, \"end\": 8922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.8989379178780313, \"rank\": 0.07012899624427375, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}, {\"begin\": 8931, \"end\": 8936, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ASEAN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9189444377104427e-29, \"text\": \"ASEAN\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ASEAN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ASEAN\"}, {\"begin\": 8941, \"end\": 8947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.0322724779098958e-12, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 9022, \"end\": 9027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.999999996052793, \"rank\": 2.225066956910153e-09, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From being custodians of public knowledge, governments are turning to architects of manufactured ignorance.\", \"from\": 9050, \"to\": 9157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid disappearing evidence, citizens are struggling to hold power to account  GenAI tools are reshaping the information environment in ways most audiences never see.\", \"from\": 9158, \"to\": 9323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the data that trains them to the labour that maintains them, their inner workings raise urgent questions for journalism and democratic accountability.\", \"from\": 9324, \"to\": 9479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Except where otherwise noted, content on this site is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license.\", \"from\": 9481, \"to\": 9607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9556, \"end\": 9610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International license\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons_license\"}, {\"begin\": 9556, \"end\": 9572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons\", \"score\": 0.9994023882572374, \"rank\": 0.0005979690963803954, \"text\": \"Creative Commons\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Creative_Commons\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use cookies to improve your experience.\", \"from\": 9609, \"to\": 9651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For an optimal experience, we recommend you enable all cookies; alternatively, you can customise which cookies you are happy for us to use.\", \"from\": 9652, \"to\": 9791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You may withdraw your consent at any time.\", \"from\": 9792, \"to\": 9834, \"entities\": []},